# Constitution Core Rules

- Keep `src/app/layout.tsx` as Server Component; avoid global `"use client"`.
- Build page from isolated sections in `src/sections/*`; no cross-section imports.
- Treat each section as a closed module: namespaced IDs/CSS/keyframes, no global selectors from section CSS.
- Preserve section visual behavior and animation timelines unless user explicitly approves changes.
- For GSAP sections, keep imperative animation logic inside `useGSAP` scoped to section root.
- Use shared core utilities only for infra concerns (`scrollRuntime`, module loading, design tokens).
- Keep DCI server-driven (resolve variants in Server Components); avoid client-side headline/content swaps.
- Prefer minimal, local diffs; do not refactor unrelated files during migration/debug tasks.
